body:
I've tried the following circuit with `Verilator 4.201 devel rev v4.032-1160-gc443e229`:

```
module multidecl(
   input  i,
   output o
);

   wire x = i;
   wire x = ~i;
   reg x = x;
   reg x = ~x;
   assign o = x;
endmodule // multidecl
```

Though the circuit does violate Section 3.13 of the 1880 standard, there are no warnings or errors, even with both `-Wall` and `-Wpedantic` enabled.
